    "recap_headline": "College of Charleston",
    "recap_text": "MT PLEASANT, S.C. \u2013\nCollege of Charleston baseball won the series with a 6-2 victory Sunday afternoon against Stony Brook.\nCharleston improved to 4-2 in the CAA and 9-10 overall while the Seawolves slip to 3-14 and 2-4 in the conference.\nCRITICAL POINTS AGAINST STONY BROOK:\nCharleston batted around in the third, scoring three runs to catapult the offense.\nJunior\nHayden Thomas\nthrew three scoreless innings in the start, holding Stony Brook to two hits and one walk.\nFreshman\nAustin Wiegandt\nfollowed Thomas, tossing two innings while punching out three.\nGraduate\nReece Holbrook\nadded insurance runs in the seventh with a two-run double to make it 6-1.\nFellow fifth year\nDylan Johnson\ntallied his ninth double of the season Sunday, going 2-for-3 with two talks.\nFreshman\nStow Rogers\nwent 2-for-3 with a walk in the victory.\nFreshman\nKaden Myers\nslammed the door, tossing two perfect innings to seal the win.\nOF NOTE:\nCharleston is now 10-2 against Stony Brook in the all-time series.\nAmman had his sixth multi-hit performance of the season Sunday.\nSweeney appeared in all three ballgames against the Seawolves, tossing 2.1 scoreless frames\nWiegandt earned his first career win Sunday.\nUP NEXT:\nCharleston hosts Clemson Tuesday, March 17 for a 6 p.m. matchup at Patriots Point.\nStanding room only tickets available for purchase by visiting\ncofcsports./tickets\nor by calling the Ticket Office at (843) 953-2632.\nFor complete coverage of Charleston baseball, follow us X (@CofCBaseball) and Instagram (@CofC_Baseball)."
